BJP could get 20-24 seats in 40-member Goa Assembly: Poll.
Goa, the poster state for majority-minority amity in Narendra Modi's India, is likely to be retained by the BJP in the February 4 Assembly election.The India Today-Axis Opinion Poll has given the BJP 20-24 seats in the 40-member Assembly - a finding that will disappoint Arvind Kejriwal's Aam Aadmi Party (AAP), which was hoping to grow beyond Delhi and north India.